         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne Botanic Garden, ¶  ¶ 28 January 1873. ¶  ¶ You may remember, noble friend, that I drew up a plan last year for an exploring expedition from the Central Australian telegraph stations to the s...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">73.01.28d</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To August Petermann</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Sammlung Perthes Archiv,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">SPA ARCH<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">PGM<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">328</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>Forschungsbibliothek Gotha der Universität Erfurt.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation by Petermann: ‘Erh. 18. März 1873 | A. 18‘ [Received 18 March 1873. Answered 18]. Petermann’s letter of reply not found. For a<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">published version</seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of this letter, see Voigt (1996), pp. 112-3.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>Melbourne<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>im<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>bot.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Garden</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">28/1/73</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Es mag Ihnen erinnerlich sein, edler Freund, dass ich<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>im vorigen Jahr den Plan etwarf<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>zu einer Entdeckungsreise von den central-australischen Telegraph Stationen nach den Quellen des Murchison-Flusses. Der muthige Giles unternahm die Reise, grossentheils aus seinen u<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>meinen eignen<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Privatkosten</hi>
               </seg>. Hiermit sende ich in Skizzenform das erste Resultat dieser Expedition,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>die alsbald fortgesetzt wird u die 2 andere<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Expeditionen<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(unter Warburton u. Gosse) ins Leben rief. Das höchst inhaltsvolle Journal des ausgezeichneten Mannes, der soweit seine Arbeit trefflich durchführte, habe ich der Regierung Südaustraliens zur Veröffentlichung <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>übersandt. Ob aber der Druck mit dieser Monatspost verschickt werden kann, steht zu bezweifeln. Mr Giles had mir das Privilegium überlassen, einige der neuen geographischen Localitäten mit Namen zu bezeichnen, u so ist auch Ihr edler Name dieser Karte dankbar aufgedruckt. Möchten Sie<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>die Güte haben eine etwaige Copirung dieser Karte in Ihren<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Mittheilungen auch dem Herrn Baron Liebig, Grafen Zeil, Dr Sonder u Dr von Heuglin zugänglich zu machen.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">Stets ehrend Ihr Freund</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">Das nächste Vordringen nach Westen soll nach der Umgehung des Amadeus Lake von Mount Olga geschehen. Die beharrliche kühne u. geschickte Bekämpfung der Schwierigkeiten die wasserlosen Wüsten zu durchdringen erinnern an Sturt u Eyre.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne Botanic Garden,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">28 January 1873.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You may remember, noble friend, that I drew up a plan last year for an exploring expedition from the Central Australian telegraph stations to the sources of the Murchison River. The courageous Giles made the expedition, financed largely by<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>his<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and my own<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">private means</hi>
               </seg>.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Ernests<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Giles's first expedition was financed by</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>George<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Duff<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Gill,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Giles’s brother-in-law<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>who is commemorated by George Gills Range<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(see Giles (1875), p.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>60).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Enclosed I<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>am sending you, in the form of a sketch,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>Sketch not found. It was published by Petermann as<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Originalkarte von E. Giles' Entdeckungsreise in Central-Australien, 1872, und Übersicht des Standpunktes der geographischen Kenntniss jener Gebiete</seg>, in<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Petermann's geographische Mittheilungen</seg>,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>vol. 19, 1873. The<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>National Library of Australia has digitised a copy:<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <ref target="http://nla.gov.au/nla.obj-232432495">
                           <seg rend="Hyperlink" style="color: #0563C1; ">http://nla.gov.au/nla.obj-232432495</seg>
                        </ref>.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the first<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>results of this expedition, which is<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>soon to be continued<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Giles set out wetwards a second time from the Overland Telegraph Line on 4 August 1873.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>which resulted in two other expeditions (under Warburton and Gosse) being<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>formed. I have sent the highly significant diary of the excellent man, who carried out his task in an admirable manner, to the South Australian Government for publication. However, it is doubtful<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>whether the publication can be sent out with this month’s mail.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>Giles's journal was made available to the press by the SA Commissioner of Crown Lands and long extracts were published in the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Advertiser</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(Adelaide), 1 February 1873, p. 2, continued 3 February, p. 2. The complete journal was published in Melbourne; see Giles (1875).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Mr<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Giles has granted me the privilege of naming some of the new localities, and as a result your noble name has been printed on the map with gratitude.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Would you have the kindness of making an eventual copy of this map<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>available<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in your<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Mittheilungen</seg>,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>also to Baron Liebig, Count Zeil, Dr Sonder, and Dr von Heuglin.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M named features that Giles had discovered as the Petermann Ranges and Mts Liebig, Zeil, Sonder and Heuglin.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Always respectfully your friend</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">The next<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>advance to the west is to be to the vicinity of Lake Amadeus<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn6" n="7">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>NT.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>from Mount Olga.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn7" n="8">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Now Kata Tjuta, NT.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The tenacious, intrepid<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and skillful struggle against the difficulties<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in penetrating<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the waterless deserts<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>is<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>reminiscent of Sturt and Eyre.</p>
         </div>
      </body>
